      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EUREKA MAC (1) was in traffic and hampered in running last time but wound up strongly to hit the frame when third (29.94) in a Grade 5 at this track. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the rails draw. Worth following up. PUERILE (4) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at Richmond over 520m behind Cumbria Jack (30.49) in a NG. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Bold showing expected. GYPSY GRACE (6) has a strong record this track and trip with two wins and two placings from six starts. Was out of the placings last time (30.45) at Wentworth Park in a NG, finishing sixth and beaten 8 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. CUMBRIA LAURA (2) can measure up with the right run.",
